section.def:
depot
                (收集站) means a depot conducted by the
            Organization;

manager
                (經理) means the person appointed by the
            Organization to be the manager of a market;

market
                (市場) means a wholesale marine fish market
            conducted by the Organization;

Organization
                (統營處) means the Fish Marketing Organization
            established under section 9 of the Ordinance;

person
                (人) includes a corporation but does not include
            an unincorporated body of persons;

register
                (登記冊) means the register which is required to be
            maintained under by-law 14;

paragraph.content:
in the case of an employee or agent of another person, the name including
                    the business name and the business and private addresses of his employer or
                    principal;

contravenes paragraph (2) of by-law 8,
                                                  by-law 9, or paragraph (2) or (3) of
                                                  by-law 17;

refuses to leave a market when ordered to do so by the
                                                manager under paragraph (1) of by-law
                                                8;

wilfully supplies any false information in an
                                                application for registration under by-law
                                                  12 or 13;

wilfully supplies any false information for the
                                                purposes of obtaining credit under paragraph (2) of
                                                  by-law 22;

in a market, obstructs the manager or an employee of
                                                the Organization in the performance of his duties;
                                                or
